EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of sanitation to collect and report data related to the unlawful posting of printed material.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of sanitation to collect and report data related to the unlawful posting of printed material.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance

EventItemMatterName: Advance posting of temporary tow-away zones.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming one thoroughfare in the Borough of Queens, Ryan Court, and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.
EventItemMatterName: Name Change, Ryan Court, Queens

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of granting the officers of the Co-op City Department of Public Safety peace officer status.
EventItemMatterName: Support of granting the officers of the Co-op City Department of Public Safety peace officer status.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution recognizing October 11 as the “Day of the Girl Child” in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Recognizing October 11 as the “Day of the Girl Child” in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Environmental Protection Agency and President Obama to fully enforce the Clean Air Act by regulating greenhouse gases in order to avert the potentially catastrophic effects of climate change.
EventItemMatterName: Enforce the Clean Air Act by regulating greenhouse gases in order to avert the potentially catastrophic effects of climate change.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning amendments to the District Plan of the Hub Third Avenue Business Improvement District that add services and modify existing services in the district, add a capital improvement program in the district, change the method of assessment upon which the district charge is based, and increase the maximum total amount to be expended for improvements in the district, and setting the date, time and place for the public hearing of the local law authorizing such changes as set forth in the amended District Plan of the Hub Third Avenue Business Improvement District.
EventItemMatterName: Hub Third Avenue BID

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning an amendment to the District Plan of the Myrtle Avenue Business Improvement District that authorizes additional services and modifies existing services for the district, and setting the date, time and place for the public hearing of the local law authorizing additional services and modifying existing services for the district.
EventItemMatterName: Myrtle Avenue BID

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Federal Government to support H.R. 3086, the Fair Wages for Workers with Disabilities Act of 2011, which phases out the issuance of special wage certificates under the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938.
EventItemMatterName: Fair Wages for Workers with Disabilities Act of 2011 (H.R. 3086)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to introduce and pass legislation that would amend the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act to allow aid to be given to houses of worship affected by Hurricane Sandy.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to introduce and pass legislation that would amend the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the New York State General Business Law to classify price gouging as a class A misdemeanor.
EventItemMatterName: NYS General Business Law to classify price gouging as a class A misdemeanor.
